useState hook React mein component ki state manage karne ke liye use hota hai. Ye ek array return karta hai jisme pehla element current state value hota hai aur dusra element state update karne ke function hota hai. 

Example: 
```javascript
import React, { useState } from 'react';

function Counter() {
    const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

    return (
        <div>
            <p>You clicked {count} times</p>
            <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>Click me</button>
        </div>
    );
}
```

useEffect hook lifecycle events ko manage karne ke liye use hotaa hai. Ye component render hone ke baad execute hota hai. 

Example:
```javascript
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';

function Example() {
    const [data, setData ] = useState([]);

    useEffect(() => {
        fetch('https://api.example.com/data')
            .then(response => response.json())
            .then(data => setData(data));
    }, []); // Empty array means this effect runs once on mount

    return <pre>{JSON.stringify(data, null, 2)}</pre>;
}
```
Is tarah se aap useState aur useEffect ka istemal karke apne React components ko manage kar sakte hain.
